emails.Subject:
Your AWS CloudShell data is scheduled for deletion on July 31, 2024
 [AWS Account: 590184145368]
emails.Body:
Hello,

Some users of this account have not used AWS CloudShell for over 110 days i=
n the ap-northeast-1 Region. On July 31, 2024 we are scheduled to delete th=
e CloudShell home directory and data of inactive users in the ap-northeast-=
1 Region.

Important: You can see the list of affected users under the Affected Resour=
ces tab in your AWS Health Dashboard [1]. To stop this deletion, users that=
 are listed in the Affected Resources tab need to launch CloudShell [2] in =
the ap-northeast-1 Region.

AWS CloudShell offers a separate home directory per AWS Region, so the dele=
tion of the home directory will occur only in the AWS Region that hasn=E2=
=80=99t been used for your CloudShell sessions in over 120 days. If you reg=
ularly use CloudShell in other AWS Regions, those separate home directories=
 will not be affected.

Please note that this notification will persist until July 31, 2024, even i=
f the aforementioned steps are completed.

For more information on persistent storage in AWS CloudShell, see Persisten=
t Storage [3]. If you have any questions or concerns, please contact AWS Pr=
emium Support [4].

References:
[1] https://phd.aws.amazon.com/phd/home?region=3Dap-northeast-1#/account/da=
shboard/scheduled-changes
[2] https://ap-northeast-1.console.aws.amazon.com/cloudshell/home?region=3D=
ap-northeast-1#
[3] https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cloudshell/latest/userguide/limits.html#per=
sistent-storage-limitations
[4] https://aws.amazon.com/support

Sincerely,
Amazon Web Services
Amazon Web Services, Inc. is a subsidiary of Amazon.com, Inc. Amazon.com is=
 a registered trademark of Amazon.com, Inc. This message was produced and d=
istributed by Amazon Web Services Inc., 410 Terry Ave. North, Seattle, WA 9=
8109-5210.

emails.Subject: [GitHub] Please download your two-factor recovery codes
emails.Body:
Hey evantann!

You=E2=80=99ve just enabled two-factor authentication.

Please take a moment to check that you have saved your recovery codes in =
a safe place. You can
download your recovery codes at:

https://github.com/settings/auth/recovery-codes

Recovery codes are the only way to access your account again. By saving y=
our
recovery codes, you=E2=80=99ll be able to regain access if you:

* Lose your phone
* Delete your authenticator app
* Change your phone number

GitHub Support will not be able to restore access to your account.

To disable two-factor authentication, visit
https://github.com/settings/security

More information about two-factor authentication can be found on GitHub H=
elp at
https://docs.github.com/articles/about-two-factor-authentication

If you have any questions, please visit https://support.github.com.

Thanks,
Your friends at GitHub

emails.Subject: [GitHub] Please verify your device
emails.Body:
Hey evantann!

A sign in attempt requires further verification because we did not recognize your device. To complete the sign in, enter the verification code on the unrecognized device.

Device: Chrome on macOS
Verification code: 116950

If you did not attempt to sign in to your account, your password may be compromised. Visit https://github.com/settings/security to create a new, strong password for your GitHub account.

If you'd like to automatically verify devices in the future, consider enabling two-factor authentication on your account. Visit https://docs.github.com/articles/configuring-two-factor-authentication to learn about two-factor authentication.

If you decide to enable two-factor authentication, ensure you retain access to one or more account recovery methods. See https://docs.github.com/articles/configuring-two-factor-authentication-recovery-methods in the GitHub Help.

Thanks,
The GitHub Team

emails.Subject: De Anza Assessment Results UPDATE on MyPortal
emails.Body:
Dear Student: 



Your Assessment Record has been updated on MyPortal!



4 Steps to View your Assessment Results:


#1. Visit MyPortal https://myportal.fhda.edu 

#2. Click on the ‘Apps’ Icon.

#3. Click on the ‘Student Registration’ Tile (typically at the very bottom of the applications listing). 

#4. Under the ‘My Records’ Menu, click on ‘See My Placement Results.’



Next Steps:


• How to Understand your Assessment Results: http://deanza.edu/assessment/results.html

• If you're registering for EWRT 1A or a related course, such as LART 250 or EWRT 1AS/EWRT 1AT, be sure to visit the EWRT Registration Tips webpage http://www.deanza.edu/english/registration.html                                    
                                  
• If you're registering for MATH 10, MATH 31 or MATH 32 with a corequisite, or companion course, be sure to visit the Math Registration Tips webpage http://deanza.edu/math/registration.html  

• Complete the New Student Orientation: http://deanza.edu/apply-and-register/apply/orientation.html 

• Meet with a Counselor and build your Educational Plan: http://deanza.edu/apply-and-register/apply/ed_plan.html



Helpful Resources:


• MyPortal Help http://deanza.edu/apply-and-register/apply/myportal_login.html 

• How to Register for Classes http://deanza.edu/apply-and-register/register/index.html 



Questions? Complete the Assessment Center contact form to send us your questions https://www.deanza.edu/assessment/contact.html 

Thank you,

Your Assessment Team



De Anza College Assessment Center

Office: Registration and Student Services Bldg. Rm. #144

Web: deanza.edu/assessment

emails.Subject: English Worship
emails.Body:
Dear English Worship Team:

Thank you for all the love and support you have given to Jing and to =
Baby Ezekiel and to myself!  We are blessed to be a part of the NLBC =
family!

Here is our program for this coming Sunday English Worship.  I will send =
my Sermon Notes ASAP.

Call to Worship:   2 Corinthians 5:17

Praise in Song:  90 Joyful, Joyful, We Adore Thee (1-2)

Intercessory Prayer

Praise in Song:  90 Joyful, Joyful, We Adore Thee (3-4)

Scripture Reading:   Revelation 21:1-5

Preparatory Hymn:  648 Love Divine, All Loves Excelling (1-4)

Sermon:  A New Beginning for the World

Offertory Hymn:  772 When We All Get to Heaven (1-4)

Ministry News:

Happy Church Anniversary!  Today we celebrate 32 Years of God=E2=80=99s =
Faithfulness at NLBC!  Praise the Lord!

Hurricane Harvey Relief:  Today we are taking a special offering to help =
people ravaged by Hurricane Harvey through the North American Mission of =
the Southern Baptist Convention. =20

Pray for Pastor Peter and Shemu:  They will travel to Indonesia and =
Taiwan from September 13 to October 15.  Please pray for God to bless =
and to protect their trip! =20

Prayer Meeting this Wednesday, September 13 at 7:30 PM.  Pastor Rich =
will begin a study of the Beatitudes (Matt. 5:1-12).

Adult English Sunday School Class:  Are there mistakes in the Bible?  =
Since the Bible was written by fallible men, does not the Bible contain =
their errors and prejudices?  No!  Next Week:  The Inerrancy of =
Scripture (Grudem Ch. 5; pp. 90-100)

Catechism Class will start in October for those who are interested in =
Baptism.  Contact Pastor Rich if you are interested!=

To:
Peter Wongka <peterwongka@yahoo.com>,
 Josh & Hanny Poli <jwhpoli@msn.com>,

 Patricia Kutadinata <patrishoei@yahoo.com>,

emails.Subject: Sermon
emails.Body:
Dear English Worship Team:

Here is our sermon for this coming Sunday.  Stephanus, please us the =
Power Point Version to cut and paste your Power Point!  Thank you!

Bulletin Version

Mark 1:9-11
A New Beginning for the World

Intro:  Today we celebrate the 32nd Anniversary of NLBC.  Hallelujah!  =
Praise the Lord!  We thank God for His goodness through all these years, =
and for His faithful servants, Pastor Peter and his wife Shemu.  They =
have given their lives to Christ by planting and growing this church.  =
We are praying for God to give them many more years to serve the Lord =
here at NLBC, and for God to give wisdom and strength to Ev. Galio and =
myself to prove ourselves faithful pastors for the next generation. =
Amen.
	Our church is named New Life Baptist Church, and I want to focus =
on that =E2=80=9CNew Life=E2=80=9D part of our church name.  It is our =
mission that people hear the Gospel of Christ here at NLBC, and that =
they experience the =E2=80=9CNew Life=E2=80=9D of salvation and eternal =
life from God, through Christ, and by the Holy Spirit.  No matter what =
kind of life people had before Christ, they can have a =E2=80=9CNew =
Life=E2=80=9D in Christ!  Hallelujah!  Praise the Lord!  So I ask the =
questions:  Where does this =E2=80=9CNew Life=E2=80=9D idea come from?  =
And what does Jesus have to do with this =E2=80=9CNew Life=E2=80=9D?

Purpose:  To Explain How the Baptism of Jesus Christ Gives a New =
Beginning for the World

Four Questions About the New Beginning for the World in the Baptism of =
Christ

1. Why Does the World Need a New Beginning? (Acts 3:19-21; Rom. 8:18-21; =
Isa. 65:17-19; 66:22; Rev. 21:1-5; 2 Pet. 3:13; 2 Cor. 5:17; Gal. 6:15)

2. What is the Significance of the Trinity in Creation and Re-Creation? =
(Gen. 1:1-3, 26; Mark 1:10-11; Matt. 28:19)

3. Why is the Holy Spirit Described like a Dove? (Gen. 8:1, 8-12)

4. Why does God the Father say that He is Well-Pleased with His Son?  =
(Gen. 1:31; 3:17; Rev. 22:3)

Preach:  Are you tired and weary of this current cursed cosmos?  Have =
you been burnt by the sin and conflict and crime and war of this wicked =
world?  Are you fed up with politicians who promise change, while things =
stay the same, or even get worse?  Are you sick of sin and sorrow?  Are =
tired of seeing your loved ones suffer and die?  Are you ready for =
something new?  Are you ready for a new life?  Come to Jesus!  He has =
the power to make you and this entire world new!

Power Point Version

Mark 1:9-11
A New Beginning for the World

Intro:  Today we celebrate the 32nd Anniversary of NLBC.  Hallelujah!  =
Praise the Lord!  We thank God for His goodness through all these years, =
and for His faithful servants, Pastor Peter and his wife Shemu.  They =
have given their lives to Christ by planting and growing this church.  =
We are praying for God to give them many more years to serve the Lord =
here at NLBC, and for God to give wisdom and strength to Ev. Galio and =
myself to prove ourselves faithful pastors for the next generation. =
Amen.
	Our church is named New Life Baptist Church, and I want to focus =
on that =E2=80=9CNew Life=E2=80=9D part of our church name.  It is our =
mission that people hear the Gospel of Christ here at NLBC, and that =
they experience the =E2=80=9CNew Life=E2=80=9D of salvation and eternal =
life from God, through Christ, and by the Holy Spirit.  No matter what =
kind of life people had before Christ, they can have a =E2=80=9CNew =
Life=E2=80=9D in Christ!  Hallelujah!  Praise the Lord!  So I ask the =
questions:  Where does this =E2=80=9CNew Life=E2=80=9D idea come from?  =
And what does Jesus have to do with this =E2=80=9CNew Life=E2=80=9D?

Purpose:  To Explain How the Baptism of Jesus Christ Gives a New =
Beginning for the World

Four Questions About the New Beginning for the World in the Baptism of =
Christ

1. Why Does the World Need a New Beginning?
	=E2=80=A2 Acts 3:19-21:  19 Repent, then, and turn to God, so =
that your sins may be wiped out, that times of refreshing may come from =
the Lord, 20 and that He may send the Messiah, who has been appointed =
for you =E2=80=94 even Jesus. 21 Heaven must receive Him until the time =
comes for God to restore everything, as He promised long ago through his =
holy prophets.
	=E2=80=A2 Rom. 8:18-21:  18 I consider that our present =
sufferings are not worth comparing with the glory that will be revealed =
in us. 19 For the creation waits in eager expectation for the children =
of God to be revealed. 20 For the creation was subjected to frustration, =
not by its own choice, but by the will of the One who subjected it, in =
hope 21 that the creation itself will be liberated from its bondage to =
decay and brought into the freedom and glory of the children of God.
=09
=E2=80=A2 Isa. 65:17-19: 17 =E2=80=9CSee, I will create New Heavens and =
a New Earth. The former things will not be remembered, nor will they =
come to mind. 18 But be glad and rejoice forever in what I will create, =
for I will create Jerusalem to be a delight and its people a joy. 19 I =
will rejoice over Jerusalem and take delight in My people; the sound of =
weeping and of crying will be heard in it no more.
	=E2=80=A2 Isa. 66:22:  =E2=80=9CAs the New Heavens and the New =
Earth that I make will endure before Me,=E2=80=9D declares the LORD, =
=E2=80=9Cso will your name and descendants endure.=E2=80=9D
	=E2=80=A2 Rev. 21:1-5:  Then I saw a New Heaven and a New Earth, =
for the first Heaven and the first Earth had passed away, and there was =
no longer any sea. 2 I saw the Holy City, the New Jerusalem, coming down =
out of Heaven from God, prepared as a Bride beautifully dressed for her =
Husband. 3 And I heard a loud voice from the throne saying, =E2=80=9CLook!=
 God=E2=80=99s dwelling place is now among the people, and He will dwell =
with them. They will be His people, and God himself will be with them =
and be their God. 4 He will wipe every tear from their eyes. There will =
be no more death or mourning or crying or pain, for the old order of =
things has passed away.=E2=80=9D 5 He who was seated on the throne said, =
=E2=80=9CI am making everything new!=E2=80=9D Then He said, =E2=80=9CWrite=
 this down, for these words are trustworthy and true.=E2=80=9D

	=E2=80=A2 2 Pet. 3:13:  In keeping with His promise we are =
looking forward to a New Heaven and a New Earth, where righteousness =
dwells.=20
	=E2=80=A2 2 Cor. 5:17:   Therefore, if anyone is in Christ, the =
New Creation has come:  The old has gone, the new is here!
	=E2=80=A2 Gal. 6:15:  Neither circumcision nor uncircumcision =
means anything; what counts is the New Creation.

2. What is the Significance of the Trinity in Creation and Re-Creation?
	=E2=80=A2 Gen. 1:1-3:  In the beginning God created the heavens =
and the earth. 2 Now the earth was formless and empty, darkness was over =
the surface of the deep, and the Spirit of God was hovering over the =
waters.  3 And God said, =E2=80=9CLet there be light,=E2=80=9D and there =
was light.
	=E2=80=A2 Gen. 1:26:  Then God said, =E2=80=9CLet us make =
mankind in our image, in our likeness=E2=80=A6=E2=80=9D
	=E2=80=A2 Mark 1:10-11:  10 Just as Jesus was coming up out of =
the water, He saw Heaven being torn open and the Spirit descending on =
Him like a dove. 11 And a Voice came from Heaven: =E2=80=9CYou are My =
Son, whom I love; with You I am well pleased.=E2=80=9D
	=E2=80=A2 Matt. 28:19:  Therefore go and make disciples of all =
nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of =
the Holy Spirit=E2=80=A6

3. Why is the Holy Spirit Described like a Dove?
	=E2=80=A2 Gen. 8:1:  But God remembered Noah and all the wild =
animals and the livestock that were with him in the ark, and he sent a =
wind [Heb. ruah, or =E2=80=9CSpirit=E2=80=9D] over the earth, and the =
waters receded.
	=E2=80=A2 Gen. 8:8-12:   Then he [Noah] sent out a dove to see =
if the water had receded from the surface of the ground. 9 But the dove =
could find nowhere to perch because there was water over all the surface =
of the earth; so it returned to Noah in the ark. He reached out his hand =

plucked olive leaf! Then Noah knew that the water had receded from the =
earth. 12 He waited seven more days and sent the dove out again, but =
this time it did not return to him.

4. Why does God the Father say that He is Well-Pleased with His Son?
	=E2=80=A2 Gen. 1:31:  God saw all that he had made, and it was =

	=E2=80=A2 Gen. 3:17:  Cursed is the ground because of you=E2=80=A6=

emails.Subject:
Perspective | Russell Moore: White supremacy angers Jesus, but does
 it anger his church? from The Washington Post
emails.Body:
Dear English Council and English Ministry Brothers and Sisters:

In light of the racial tensions raised by the deadly conflict in =
Charlottesville, Virginia last Saturday, and the subsequent =
controversies raised by the statements of our political leaders, I feel =
it is wise to consider what our Lord Jesus teaches about race and the =
Gospel.

Here is a link to an opinion written by Dr. Russell Moore, the president =
of the Ethics & Religious Liberty Commission of the Southern Baptist =
Convention.  I think the article is helpful for us to trust and obey the =
Lord Jesus, and to grow in righteous anger against the great sin of =
racism.

http://wapo.st/2w6DBca?tid=3Dss_mail&utm_term=3D.ee41cea231bd

Please feel free to contact me with any questions or concerns about this =
article, or about the racial conflicts of this past week!

May God bring peace and racial reconciliation through the Gospel of His =
Son, the Lord Jesus Christ!  Amen.

In Christ,
Rich=

emails.Body:
Dear Baptism Class:

Pastor Peter has asked me to interview you before this coming Sunday.

Please let me know if you are available for a video or phone call =
interview this Friday (7-10 PM) or Saturday (2-4 PM)!  Also, please let =
me know what video conferencing format you prefer to use (e.g. Skype, =
Facetime or Facebook)!  Thank you!

Also, you will still have a written Exam this coming Sunday.  We will =
continue our Class studies after the Christmas Service into January.

Here are the interview questions:

1. What is the Gospel?

2. Do you admit that you a sinner?  Do you believe that you deserve the =
judgment of God for your sins?  Please explain.

3. Do you believe that Jesus Christ died for your sins and rose from the =
dead?

4. Have you asked God to forgive you of your sins in Jesus=E2=80=99 =
name?

5. Do you confess Jesus Christ as Lord of your life?  Do you desire to =
live in obedience to Him?

6. How did you become a Christian?  Please explain.

6. Why do you want to be baptized?

(Kaylen, I have cc=E2=80=99d you so that you can also prepare for your =
eventual interview prior to Easter baptism.  I will not schedule you for =
this Christmas baptism, so do not worry about being interviewed this =
weekend.)

In Christ,
Rich=

emails.Subject: Sermon
emails.Body:
Dear English Worship Team:

Here is our Sermon for this coming Mother=E2=80=99s Day.  Be nice to your Mo=
ms!

Proverbs 31:10-31
A Wife of Noble Character Who Can Find? She Is Worth Far More Than Rubies

Intro: This past Friday marks the Six Month Anniversary for Jing's and my ma=
rriage. Hallelujah! Praise the Lord! And we are going to have a baby too! Pl=
ease pray for God to give us a healthy and strong baby! Thank you! When I pr=
oposed to Jing, I read from this very Scripture before asking her to marry m=
e. And today I want to preach this text to thank God, and to bless my wife, a=
nd to honor all the Christian women here.

The Context: Proverbs is addressed to young single men who need both wisdom a=
nd a wife.

A Wife of Noble Character is a Blessing from God (Prov. 18:22; 12:4a; 19:14)=


A Beautiful But Quarrelsome Wife is Hard to Live With (Prov. 11:22; 19:13; 2=
1:9, 19; 25:24; 27:15-16)

What To Look for in a Wife (Prov. 31:10-31; an acrostic poem): There is no d=
escription of a woman's outward physical beauty; instead the focus is on her=
 devotion to God and her hard work and her wisdom and her compassion. In oth=
er words, a godly wife is known and admired for her character, not for her l=
ooks (1 Sam. 16:7; 1 Pet. 3:3-4).

She is a blessing to her husband (vv. 11-12, 23, 28-29, 31).

She is a business woman (vv. 13-14, 18, 24).

She is a hard worker (vv. 15, 17).

She is an investor (v. 16).

She is a compassionate and merciful giver (v. 20).

She is a planner (v. 25).

She is a teacher (v. 26).

She is a manager (v. 27).

She is a wife and a mother (v. 28).

She is a woman who fears God (v. 30).

She is a woman who should be praised and emulated (vv. 29, 31).

emails.Subject: Sermon
emails.Body:
Dear English Worship Team:

Here is our Sermon for this Sunday:  Kelvin, please use the bottom =
version to cut and paste for our Power Point!  Thank you

Bulletin Version

2 Samuel 5:17-25
The LORD Fights for His People

Intro:  What do you think about when you think about God?  What kind of =
God do you worship?  Do you picture God as a doting grandma in the sky?  =
Do you picture God like a divine fortune cookie, who may be able to give =
you a positive prediction and good luck for your daily fantasies?  Do =
you think of God as a great unknown, Someone who might be real, but who =
also might be the collective belief of uneducated and small-minded =
religious hypocrites?  Clearly, such thoughts about God are not worthy =
of His glory.  So have you ever thought of the predominant metaphor of =
God in the OT, namely that God is a Divine Warrior who fights for His =
people?

Purpose:  To Picture God as the Divine Warrior Who Fights For His People

Outline of 2 Samuel 5:17-25
A. David Defeats the Philistines in the Valley of Rephaim (vv. 17-21)
	1. The Philistines Attack David. (vv. 17-18)
	2. David Inquires of the LORD. (v. 19a)
	3. The LORD Directs David=E2=80=99s Attack. (v. 19b)
	4. David Defeats the Philistines with the LORD=E2=80=99s Help. =
(v. 20)
	5. The Philistines Lose Their Idols. (v. 21).=20
A=E2=80=99. David Defeats the Philistines in the Valley of Rephaim a =
Second Time (vv. 22-25)
	1. The Philistines Attack David Again. (v. 22)
	2. David Inquires of the LORD (v. 23a)
	3. The LORD Directs David=E2=80=99s Attack. (v. 23b-24)
	4. David Drives Away the Philistines. (v. 25)

Theology of the Divine Warrior

1. The LORD is a Warrior. (Exod. 15:3; Jos. 5:13-15; 2 Sam. 22:7-16)
=09
2. The LORD Fights for His People. (Exod. 14:13-14; Deut. 20:1-4; 1 Sam. =
17:45-47; 2 Sam. 22:17-20, 47-50)

3. Jesus is the Divine Warrior To Come.  (Rev. 19:11-21)

Life Lessons
1. Do you regularly inquire of God for guidance in your decision making?
2. Do you trust and obey the Lord when He gives you guidance?
3. Do you believe that the Lord is your Divine Warrior, who will fight =
for you and conquer your enemies?
4. Do you give God all the glory for every victory in your life?

Power Point Version

2 Samuel 5:17-25
The LORD Fights For His People

Intro:  What do you think about when you think about God?  What kind of =
God do you worship?  Do you picture God as a doting grandma in the sky?  =
Do you picture God like a divine fortune cookie, who may be able to give =
you a positive prediction and good luck for your daily fantasies?  Do =
you think of God as a great unknown, Someone who might be real, but who =
also might be the collective belief of uneducated and small-minded =
religious hypocrites?  Clearly, such thoughts about God are not worthy =
of His glory.  So have you ever thought of the predominant metaphor of =
God in the OT, namely that God is a Divine Warrior who fights for His =
people?

Purpose:  To Picture God as the Divine Warrior Who Fights For His People

Outline of 2 Samuel 5:17-25
A. David Defeats the Philistines in the Valley of Rephaim (vv. 17-21)
	1. The Philistines Attack David. (vv. 17-18)
	2. David Inquires of the LORD. (v. 19a)
	3. The LORD Directs David=E2=80=99s Attack. (v. 19b)
	4. David Defeats the Philistines with the LORD=E2=80=99s Help. =
(v. 20)
	5. The Philistines Lose Their Idols. (v. 21).=20
A=E2=80=99. David Defeats the Philistines in the Valley of Rephaim a =
Second Time (vv. 22-25)
	1. The Philistines Attack David Again. (v. 22)
	2. David Inquires of the LORD (v. 23a)
	3. The LORD Directs David=E2=80=99s Attack. (v. 23b-24)
	4. David Drives Away the Philistines. (v. 25)

Theology of the Divine Warrior

1. The LORD is a Warrior.
	=E2=80=A2 Exod. 15:3:  The LORD is a warrior; the LORD is His =
name.
	=E2=80=A2 Jos. 5:13-15:  13 Now when Joshua was near Jericho, he =
looked up and saw a Man standing in front of him with a drawn sword in =
His hand. Joshua went up to Him and asked, =E2=80=9CAre You for us or =
for our enemies?=E2=80=9D 14 =E2=80=9CNeither,=E2=80=9D He replied, =
=E2=80=9Cbut as Commander of the Army of the LORD I have now come.=E2=80=9D=
 Then Joshua fell facedown to the ground in reverence, and asked Him, =
=E2=80=9CWhat message does my Lord have for His servant?=E2=80=9D 15 The =
Commander of the LORD=E2=80=99s Army replied, =E2=80=9CTake off your =
sandals, for the place where you are standing is holy.=E2=80=9D And =
Joshua did so.
	=E2=80=A2 2 Sam. 22:7-16
=09
2. The LORD Fights for His People.
	=E2=80=A2 Ex. 14:13-14:  13 Moses answered the people, =E2=80=9CDo=
 not be afraid. Stand firm and you will see the deliverance the LORD =
will bring you today. The Egyptians you see today you will never see =
again. 14 The LORD will fight for you; you need only to be still.=E2=80=9D=

	=E2=80=A2 Deut. 20:1-4:  When you go to war against your enemies =
and see horses and chariots and an army greater than yours, do not be =
afraid of them, because the LORD your God, who brought you up out of =
Egypt, will be with you. 2 When you are about to go into battle, the =
priest shall come forward and address the army. 3 He shall say: =E2=80=9CH=
ear, Israel: Today you are going into battle against your enemies. Do =
not be fainthearted or afraid; do not panic or be terrified by them. 4 =
For the LORD your God is the One who goes with you to fight for you =
against your enemies to give you victory.=E2=80=9D
	=E2=80=A2 1 Sam. 17:45-47:  45 David said to the Philistine, =
=E2=80=9CYou come against me with sword and spear and javelin, but I =
come against you in the name of the LORD Almighty, the God of the armies =
of Israel, whom you have defied. 46 This day the LORD will deliver you =
into my hands, and I=E2=80=99ll strike you down and cut off your head. =
This very day I will give the carcasses of the Philistine army to the =
birds and the wild animals, and the whole world will know that there is =
a God in Israel. 47 All those gathered here will know that it is not by =
sword or spear that the LORD saves; for the battle is the LORD=E2=80=99s, =
and He will give all of you into our hands.
	=E2=80=A2 2 Sam. 22:17-20; 47-50


3. Jesus is the Divine Warrior To Come.
	=E2=80=A2 Rev. 19:11-21

Life Lessons
1. Do you regularly inquire of God for guidance in your decision making?
2. Do you trust and obey the Lord when He gives you guidance?
3. Do you believe that the Lord is your Divine Warrior, who will fight =
for you and conquer your enemies?
4. Do you give God all the glory for every victory in your life?=

emails.Subject: Scripture Memorization
emails.Body:
Dear Catechism Class:

Please work on your scripture memorization for this coming Sunday=E2=80=99=
s Youth Group!  You must memorize the following verses from the NIV =
2011, and you have them PERFECTLY memorized.  Paraphrases of these verse =
are not acceptable!

I am working on these Bible verses myself, and I am expecting our =
assistants, Stephanie and Stanley, to memorize them perfectly too.

Therefore, if anyone is in Christ, the new creation has come: The old =
has gone, the new is here! - 2 Corinthians 5:17

If we confess our sins, He is faithful and just and will forgive us our =
sins and purify us from all unrighteousness. - 1 John 1:9

For it is by grace you have been saved, through faith=E2=80=94and this =
is not from yourselves, it is the gift of God=E2=80=94not by works, so =
that no one can boast. - Ephesians 2:8-9

I have been crucified with Christ and I no longer live, but Christ lives =
in me. The life I now live in the body, I live by faith in the Son of =
God, who loved me and gave Himself for me. - Galatians 2:20

Salvation is found in no one else, for there is no other Name under =
heaven given to mankind by which we must be saved. - Acts 4:12

For all have sinned and fall short of the glory of God. - Romans 3:23

For the wages of sin is death, but the gift of God is eternal life in =
Christ Jesus our Lord. - Romans 6:23

I am praying for God to prepare for your Catechism Final on Sunday, =
April 9.

In Christ,
Rich=

emails.From: "'Peter Lu' via All Parents and Scouts" <Team@bsatroop737.org>
emails.Subject: Volunteers needed for Saturday December 22
emails.Body:
Hello Troop,

City of Walnut has giving us the permission to set up a =
map/compass/orienteering course at the Creekside Park. Mr. Ken Tragraz =
and Mr. Tom Pedersen have done much of the planning and logistics on =
this project. We are now in the final stage of the project, =
implementation. We need some scouts to assist us setting up the course. =
If you can assist, please meet us at 780 N. Creekside Drive, Walnut, CA =
91789 at 7am. It may take 4-5 hours to complete.=20

Once the course is set up, it will provide our troop as well as other =
troops a safe and year around training course. Any instructors or scouts =
who are interested to become a subject matter expert in =
map/compass/orienteering are highly recommended to participate in =
building the course so you may be familiar with all the details. In =
addition, scouts who become subject matter experts and interested in =
public speaking will have the opportunity to be part of the instructor =
team when City of Walnut starts to offer the course to its residents in =
the future.

Thank you to Mr. Tragraz and Mr. Pedersen for getting this project off =
the ground. I hope to see many of you out there.  =20

Thanks,

Peter Lu
Scoutmaster, Troop 737=

emails.From: "'Peter Lu' via All Parents and Scouts" <Team@bsatroop737.org>
emails.Subject: High Adventure with Troop 789
emails.Body:
Hello Troop,

Troop 789 is planning a high adventure to Philmont, New Mexico in 2019. =
They have two spots available to scouts who is at least 14 years of age =
by July of 2019 and ideally above rank of 2nd class. Anyone who is =
interested, please come see me for more information. Below are some =
general information for you to consider:

1) Total of 14 days, first and last day travel and 12 days at Philmont, =
leaving Friday, July 19, 2019
2) Cost per scout is $1,950 (not including the $300 train ride, $50 bus =
ride, and meals for first and last day of travel)
3) Training starts in January, 2019 with one overnight hiking beginning =
of the month and a day hike at the end of month, each month until June, =
2019.=20
4) Total 12 members, 9 scouts and 3 registered adults

Thanks,

Peter Lu
Scoutmaster Troop 737=

emails.From: "'Peter Lu' via All Parents and Scouts" <Team@bsatroop737.org>

emails.Body:
Hi Scouts,

Out troop will be hosting this year=E2=80=99s District dinner on =
Saturday, February 3, 2018 at the Walnut Senior Center.  We need 20 to =
30 scouts to assist with the event.  This is our chance to show our =
pride to the council as well as other troop leaders in the areas.  =
You=E2=80=99ll be helping setting up the tables, flag ceremony, food =
serving , and clean up from approximately 3pm to 9pm.  Troop will =
provide food and drink for the scouts.  All scouts must be in full class =
A uniform.  Your participation is highly encourged especially for the =
older scouts.  If you can assist, please send me an email.

Thank you,

Peter Lu
Scoutmaster, Troop 737=

and ASPL will further develop your leadership skill by leading our ever =
growing troop into the future. Having a leadership position under your =

board members. If you are ready to take on the challenge, please submit =

Here are this week's five links that are worth your time:

rom 1981 was 16 kilobytes. And yet these devs are able to build platformers=

e of the techniques developers used to code these games. (1 hour watch): ht=
tps://www.freecodecamp.org/news/20-award-winning-games-explained-code-break=
down/

2. How to build your own Instagram mobile app using JavaScript, React Nativ=
e, Redux, Firebase, and Expo. Your app will include an authentication syste=

reecodecamp.org/news/build-an-instagram-clone-with-react-native-firebase-fi=
restore-redux-and-expo/

3. The OSI Model is a powerful way of thinking about computer networks. And=
 in this network engineering crash course, Chloe will explain how all 7 of =
its layers work =E2=80=93 in plain English. You don't have to administer a =
server farm to be able to understand this model. (20 minute read): https://=

glish/

ation. And in this tutorial, Cedd explains some key time complexity concept=

etching your mind. Here are 730 free online programming and computer scienc=
e courses from universities around the world to help you get started in the=
 new year. (browsable list): https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/free-online-=
programming-cs-courses/


Quote of the Week: =E2=80=9CThe golden rule of level design - finish your f=
irst level last.=E2=80=9D - John Romero (co-creator of DOOM)


2021 is going to be a big year for the freeCodeCamp community. A big thank =
you to the 6,775 kind people who support our nonprofit's mission with their=

t up a donation. Every little bit helps: https://www.freecodecamp.org/donat=
e/


Happy coding.

emails.Body:

base Design, Distributed Data Processing, NoSQL, and more. (25 hour YouTube=

base-course-for-free/

2. We also published a full-length book that will teach you Python basics. =
This beginner's handbook includes hundreds of Python syntax examples. You c=
an bookmark it and read it in your browser, or download a PDF version. (ful=
l book): https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/the-python-handbook/

3. And I swear I'm not trying to overload you, but we also published a 6-ho=
ur course on how to configure and operate Linux servers. If you want to bec=
ome a SysAdmin or DevOps, this should give your server skills a big boost. =
(6 hour YouTube course): https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/linux-server-cou=
rse-system-configuration-and-operation/

4. For some lighter reading, Jacob went way back in time to look at the fir=
st commit to the Git project's codebase. You can learn some C fundamentals =
by reading Linus Torvalds' original code, which now underpins the world's m=
ost widely-used version control system. (25 minute read): https://www.freec=
odecamp.org/news/boost-programming-skills-read-git-code/

5. And since you just finished reading that Python book =E2=80=93 you did f=
inish reading it, didn't you? =F0=9F=99=82 =E2=80=93 why not learn how to u=
se Python's powerful Flask Web Development Framework. You can code along at=
 home and build your own ecommerce website. (6 hour YouTube course): https:=
//www.freecodecamp.org/news/learn-the-flask-python-web-framework-by-buildin=
g-a-market-platform/

And a quick update on the freeCodeCamp Data Science Curriculum Pledge drive=
: we're now up to 1,387 kind people who have donated. And we're over half w=
ay to our goal. We'll use these funds to hire experienced math and computer=
 science teachers to design these new interactive coding projects.

I've got a full curriculum outline ready for you, with tons of data science=
 and machine learning projects all mapped out. If you haven't already, take=
 a moment to read this. You can become a part of this as well: https://www.=
freecodecamp.org/news/building-a-data-science-curriculum-with-advanced-math=
-and-machine-learning/

That's all for this week. It has been a busy week at freeCodeCamp.


Quote of the Week: =E2=80=9CYou can have data without information. But you =
cannot have information without data.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=93 Daniel Keys Moran


Happy coding.

- Quincy Larson

emails.Subject: Holiday Greeting
emails.Body:
Hello Scouts and Parents,

As we celebrate this Thanksgiving holiday, I couldn=E2=80=99t be more proud o=
f all the achievements that our scouts accomplished as a Troop and many of t=
he contributions made by our adult leaders. We are one of the Troops with th=
e most participants in both Camporee and Summer camp. We have performed nume=
rous service and Eagle projects for our community, and we have three scouts r=
eached the rank of Eagle this year.

For the scouts, as we get ready for the new year, we want to continue learni=
ng and leading as a Troop. I encourage all scouts to consider taking on a le=
adership role to challenge yourself. Applications for SPL and ASPL are due s=
oon. Are you ready to showcase your skills? We=E2=80=99ll guide you along th=
e way.=20

For the parents, you play an important part in your boy=E2=80=99s life. Scou=
ts tend to be more active in the Troop when the parents are involved. For th=
e upcoming year, Mr. Juarez will be nominated at our next parent committee m=
eeting as the next scoutmaster for our Troop. As a Life scout himself, Mr. J=
uarez is knowledgeable in many aspects of scouting. I thank Mr. Juarez for h=
is willingness to volunteer his time. I will continue to assist the Troop as=
 one of the assistant scoutmasters.

Thank you all for all the support that you have giving to scouting. I am Loo=
king forward to another exciting year in 2019.

Sincerely,

Peter Lu
Scoutmaster, Troop 737

emails.Subject: Safety Concern
emails.Body:
Hello Troop,

I want to remind all the scouts and parents to be aware of their surrounding=
 before, during, and after our weekly meeting both at the Lemon Creek Park a=
nd Susanne Middle School. At the Park, it gets dark after 8pm, and there are=
 many unknown strangers in the area.=20

For the safety of our scouts, I would like to have all the parents to pick u=
p their boys at the meeting site. No scout should be alone waiting at the cu=
rbside. Safety of our scouts is our utmost priority.=20

If there is any question or concern, please reach out to me or any of the ad=
ult leaders. Thank you.

Peter Lu
Scoutmaster, Troop 737

emails.Subject:
Learn Python data analysis [free 10-hour course on Pandas, NumPy, and
 Matplotlib]
emails.Body:
This week's five links that are worth your time:

1. freeCodeCamp just published a free 10-hour Python Data Analysis course. =
You can learn Pandas, Numpy, Matplotlib, and other key data science tools. =
This course is taught by a former Twitter engineer, IIT grad, and ACM ICPC =
world finalist. (10 hour YouTube course): https://www.freecodecamp.org/news=
/how-to-analyze-data-with-python-pandas/

2. How to use LinkedIn to get your first developer job =E2=80=93 an in-dept=
h step-by-step guide (30 minute read): https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/li=
nkedin-handbook-get-your-first-dev-job/

3. What is fuzzing? And why does Google have 30,000 servers dedicated to co=
ntinuously fuzzing their own applications? Learn all about this intriguing =
software testing approach. (7 minute read): https://www.freecodecamp.org/ne=
ws/whats-fuzzing-fuzz-testing-explained/

4. Did you know that you can use spreadsheets as a database? Here's how to =
turn Google Sheets into your own REST API and use it to power a React app (=
10 minute read): https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/react-and-googlesheets/

5. All of the most useful JavaScript array methods in one place, and explai=
ned with helpful examples (25 minute read): https://www.freecodecamp.org/ne=
ws/complete-introduction-to-the-most-useful-javascript-array-methods/


Quote of the Week: =E2=80=9CI never guess. It is a capital mistake to theor=
ize before one has data. Insensibly one begins to twist facts to suit theor=
ies, instead of theories to suit facts.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=93 Sir Arthur Conan=
 Doyle


A quick update on our data science curriculum pledge drive. So far the free=
CodeCamp community has raised $45,256 from 881 kind donors. Our goal is to =
raise $150,000, all of which will be 100% matched by educator-turned-benefa=
ctor Darrell Silver. This means that if you donate, say $50, it will transl=
ate into $100 worth of budget for us to hire experienced teachers to design=
 these math and machine learning courses. Learn more and get involved: http=
s://www.freecodecamp.org/news/building-a-data-science-curriculum-with-advan=
ced-math-and-machine-learning/


Happy coding.

- Quincy Larson

Teacher at https://www.freecodecamp.org
I share useful things on Twitter at https://www.twitter.com/ossia

If these emails aren't worth your time, you can turn them off: https://www.=
freecodecamp.org/ue/H4P0G5gJRyslxTb8XJ1D

emails.Subject: Python VS JavaScript =?UTF-8?B?4oCT?= what are the key differences?
emails.Body:
Here are this week's five links that are worth your time:

1. Python VS JavaScript =E2=80=93 what are the key differences? Estefania d=
ives deep into both languages to explore how they handle loops, conditional=
 logic, data types, input/output, and more. These are the two biggest langu=
age ecosystems, and they're rapidly shaping the software development as a w=
hole. (20 minute read): https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/python-vs-javascr=
ipt-what-are-the-key-differences-between-the-two-popular-programming-langua=
ges/

2. The C language =E2=80=93 and its close cousin C++ =E2=80=93 are great fo=
r game development and other computationally intensive programming tasks. T=
his free full-length course will show you how to code advanced data structu=
res "close to the metal" right in C. (10 hour YouTube course): https://www.=
freecodecamp.org/news/understand-data-structures-in-c-and-cpp/

3. A developer and hiring manager shares what she looks for when reviewing =
job applicants' r=C3=A9sum=C3=A9s. (7 minute read): https://www.freecodecam=
p.org/news/how-to-get-your-first-dev-job/

4. How hex code colors work =E2=80=93 and how you can choose the right colo=
rs for your designs without the need for a color picker tool. (8 minute rea=
d): https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/how-hex-code-colors-work-how-to-choos=
e-colors-without-a-color-picker/

5. When I started learning to code back in 2012, podcasts were a key part o=
f my journey. Here are 14 developer podcasts that have taught me the most a=
bout tools, concepts, and an engineering mindset. You can listen and learn =
while you commute, exercise, or just relax. (10 minute read): https://www.f=
reecodecamp.org/news/best-tech-podcasts-for-software-developers/


Quote of the Week: =E2=80=9CAny app that can be written in JavaScript will =
eventually be written in JavaScript.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=93 Atwood's Law


Thanks to all of you who are now supporting our nonprofit's mission. For th=
e first time ever, we now have more than 7,000 monthly supporters. We are h=
onored and humbled to create these free learning resources for you, your fa=
milies, and neighbors around the world. If you haven't started donating to =
freeCodeCamp.org yet, you can start today: https://www.freecodecamp.org/don=
ate


Happy coding.

- Quincy Larson

Teacher at https://www.freecodecamp.org

emails.Subject: Freshman Survey Reminder
emails.Body:
Dear Evan,=0D=0A=0D=0ARecently we sent you a request to participa=
te in an important survey about incoming college students conduct=
ed for Mt. SAC by the Higher Education Research Institute (HERI) =
at UCLA.  This survey asks your opinion on many items relevant to=
 examining the impact of college.  Every fall, students from hund=
reds of colleges and universities across the country are asked to=
 participate in this same survey.  It asks about your expectation=
s for college, your academic habits and experiences, what influen=
ced your college choice, your goals and values, and how you spend=
 your time.=0D=0A=0D=0AResults from this survey are used by facul=
ty and administrators at Mt. SAC and by higher education research=
ers to understand and improve the undergraduate college experienc=
e. This is especially important in light of the global pandemic a=
nd the drastic changes that have resulted in the college experien=
ce.=0D=0A=0D=0APlease consider adding your opinions and experienc=
es to this important project.=0D=0A=0D=0AThe website for this sur=
vey is: https://www.drcsurveys.com/CIRPFreshmanSurvey2020/et.aspx=
?Logon=3DV44VU7P=0D=0A=0D=0ASimply click on this address to go di=
rectly to the survey. If this does not work, "copy and paste" thi=
s address into the address bar of your Internet Browser.=0D=0A=0D=0A=
Your participation in this survey is completely voluntary. Your r=
esponses to the questionnaire indicate your consent to participat=
e (please read the "Survey Information Sheet" on the survey websi=
te for more information).=0D=0A=0D=0AThank you for participating =
in this very important survey!=0D=0A=0D=0ASincerely,=0D=0A=0D=0AL=
isa DiDonato=0D=0AEducational Research Assessment Analyst,=0D=0AM=
t. San Antonio College

emails.Subject: Re: FRS003: Assignment Comments and Late Assignment
emails.Body:
Hello Evan,

The website is just fine, but please follow the link I included in the 
assignment to see how I would like for you to reference websites in the 
future.

As for the Perusall assignment, I haven't figured out how to get the 
grades to sync with Canvas automatically, so I entered them manually. 
Apparently I did that four days after the assignment was due, and it was 
marked as late. Thanks for letting me know about this, but it should be 
resolved now.

Regards,

Jeremy Mason

> Thanks,
> Evan

emails.Subject: FAFSA Confirmation Page E-mail
emails.Body:
Congratulations, EVAN!

Your 2021-2022 FAFSA  was successfully submitted to Federal Student Aid.

Confirmation Number: F 10109113505 02/28/2021 10:55:05.
Data Release Number (DRN): 7345

What Happens Next

- You will be notified when your FAFSA is processed.
- Your FAFSA information will be made available to your school(s), and they will use it to determine the aid you may be =
eligible to receive.
- Your school(s) will contact you if they need more information or when they are ready to discuss your financial aid =
award.
- If you have questions about your financial aid package, contact your school(s)

Eligibility Information

Estimated Expected Family Contribution (EFC)=3D 020490
=0aThe EFC is a measure of how much you can contribute to the cost of your education. Schools use your EFC to determine your federal student aid eligibility.=0a=0aThe EFC is not how much aid you will receive or how much you have to pay for college.=0a=0aBased on the eligibility criteria you may be eligible for the following:=0a=0aDirect Stafford Loan Estimate - $6,500=0a=0aYou may also be eligible to receive other federal, state, or institutional grants, scholarships, and/or work-study.=0a=0aIn addition, you should learn about federal tax benefits for education https://studentaid.gov/resources/tax-benefits, including the American Opportunity Tax Credit (AOTC).=
=0a=0a=
If you have questions, visit StudentAid.gov/fafsahelp.

Thank You,

U.S. Department of Education
Federal Student Aid

Response from the College Board - Case 06512420    [
 ref:_00DF05YBt._5003k1gHiof:ref ]
emails.Body:
Thank you, Evan Tan, for contacting the College Board.

We have received your escalations request in regard to your Nov 2, 2019 SAT=
 Scores. We will be more than happy to assist you and provide you with some=
 information.

Your Nov 2, 2019 SAT scores are now available.

You can view and send scores by logging in to your www.collegeboard.com acc=
ount with your username and password. Select "My Tests" on your "My Organiz=
er" page. On the right hand side of this section you will find many links. =
You will then scroll down and select "My SAT Scores." This selection will b=
ring you to "My SAT." Scroll down until you find the "My Scores" section, w=
here your scores will be displayed. You may click on "Understand Your Test =
Performance" to view and / or print your full score report including your e=
ssay.

If you do not remember your username, please use the "Forgot your Username"=
 link located within the "My Organizer" box. If you do not remember your pa=
ssword, please use the "Forgot your Password" link. You may change your pas=
sword or e-mail address, but not the user name.

The username associated with your account is:   XDLEARNER1

Please check to make sure your local desktop meets all of the following tec=
hnical requirements for accessing the College Board web site:=20

=95=09Internet Explorer 10.0 or higher (Windows computers only)=20
=95=09The current version of Firefox (this browser updates automatically)=
=20
=95=09The current version of Google Chrome (this browser updates automatica=
lly)=20
=95=09Safari 5.0 or higher (Macintosh computers only)=20

Some features require the Flash browser plug in. You can install it at http=
://get.adobe.com/flashplayer/

Remember: You'll need to enable cookies on your computer.

If you are unable to remember your password from your hint, or if you need =
assistance, you can also contact Customer Service Department, to learn your=
 scores once they are released. There is a telephone service fee of $15.00 =
for this service and is payable using a Visa, MasterCard, American Express,=
 Discover, Diners, or JCB (Japanese Credit Bureau) credit card. We also acc=
ept debit cards that have a Visa or MasterCard logo.=20

For further information or assistance, please feel free to call us at 1 (86=
6) 756-7346 (Domestic), 001 (212) 713-7789 (International), Monday through =
Friday, from 8:00 a.m. to 9:00 p.m. (Eastern Time) or visit us at www.colle=
geboard.org.

Thank You,

Paul
Agent ID #190349
The College Board Service Center

emails.Subject: Re: Newest Eagle Scout from Troop 737
emails.Body:
Dear All,

Through this journey as a scout, I have learned many things from many =
people. As my life grew from a scout to an Eagle Scout, many people were =
there to support me, guide me, and teach me. I would like to thank all =
of those people such as adult leaders, friends, family, and fellow =
scouts who have helped me on this journey. I am glad to announce my =
proud accomplishment as an Eagle Scout and hope to help others achieve =
this goal. I will be continuing scouting throughout schooling and =
hopefully life.=20

Once again, I would like to thank all of those who have helped me =
achieve this accomplishment and I hope that I can do the same to other =
fellow scouts.

If anyone has any questions or are in need of help for Eagle (or =
anything), please do not hesitate to ask.=20

Sincerely,
Eric Han

d. =0A=0AThe event is sold out which means that we need all the s=
taff we can get to support both the kitchen and the miscellaneous=

ow events during the year. Please try and arrive on Friday by 7pm=

If you need more information contact me at brian.t.wilder@mac.com=
=0A=0AWe need your support, so see you this weekend.=0A=0A=0A=0A=0A=

er.  We will be standing along the side of our new Ordeal candida=
tes as we provide service to our council by assisting with painti=
ng, clean up, and maintenance. Please be sure to bring clothing t=
hat you don't mind accidentally spilling paint on.  If you have a=
 6 foot step latter please bring it along with you so that we can=
 paint some of the taller items on site.=0A=0AWe ask that you sig=
n up by tonight so that we have a final head count, so that our f=
ood service can purchase the right amount of food.=0A=0AIt appear=
s that the doubleknot registration is closed, but if you plan on =
attending please send Brian Wilder an email indicating that you p=
lan on attending, so that we can purchase the right amount of foo=
d for the weekend. brian.t.wilder@mac.com=0A=0ASee you all there.=
.. =0A=0AWWW,=0A=0ARobert Collings=0ATuku 'ut Lodge Adviser=0A562=

emails.Subject: Troop Gear
emails.Body:
Hello Troop,
This is Wesley Ong, one of your current quartermasters for this term. As we a=
pproach the next outing, we request that all troop gear including stoves, pa=
trol boxes, tents and tarps be returned the next meeting, June 4th. The late=
st you may return troop gear is the Monday of the following week, June 11. M=
ake sure the item which you plan to return is clean, meaning there is no oil=
, food remnants, dirt, and please make sure the gear is dry to prevent the g=
rowing of mold. This would greatly help us quartermasters.=20

Thank you,
Wesley=20=

contact: "'Kevin Cho' via All Parents and Scouts"

emails.From: "'Kevin Cho' via All Parents and Scouts" <Team@bsatroop737.org>
emails.Subject: Eagle Scout Service Project Tomorrow
emails.Body:
Good evening Troop,

I hope everyone had a good week. This is just a reminder for my Eagle Scout P=
roject tomorrow at Suzanne Middle School from 7:00 am to approximately 4:00 p=
m. I will have a quick breakfast and lunch provided during the project.=20

The project will consist of sanding and painting two coats of paint onto the=
 eight bench sets within the school=E2=80=99s campus along with planting 14 p=
lants into the planter that is beside the main office.=20

Scouts and other helpers are not required to stay for the entire time as I u=
nderstand Saturdays tend to be busy for everyone. Once again, I=E2=80=99d li=
ke to reiterate that helpers will receive service project hours for however l=
ong they choose to staying which can then be written on their Service Projec=
t Log in their scout book.

If you plan on helping, please remember to wear your class B shirts (red sco=
ut shirts) if you have one along with pants and shoes that you don=E2=80=99t=
 mind getting paint on. Also if you can, please bring an outdoor broom, dust=
pan, and or work gloves.=20

Thank you and I hope to see you there!

Sincerely,
Kevin Cho

emails.From: "'Kevin Cho' via All Parents and Scouts" <Team@bsatroop737.org>
emails.Subject: Eagle Project Additional Info
emails.Body:
Also, if you plan on participating in the Eagle Project this Saturday, pleas=
e keep in mind you=E2=80=99re outfits may get dirty by paint or otherwise so=
 please wear your red Class B shirts and pants/shoes that you don=E2=80=99t m=
ind getting dirty. Please also keep in mind that it may be sunny that day so=
 remember to bring any sun protection that you may need.

*YOU DO NOT NEED TO STAY FOR THE ENTIRE TIME* if you have obligations later i=
n the day then you do not need to stay for the entirety of the project.=

emails.From: "'Kevin Cho' via All Parents and Scouts" <Team@bsatroop737.org>
emails.Subject: Eagle Project Success and Thanks
emails.Body:
Hello Troop! I just wanted to thank everyone that came out today and helped m=
ake my Eagle Project a success! We ended 2 hours ahead of schedule due to th=
e hard work of both the adult and scout participants. Thankfully no one was i=
njured or hurt at all during the project and clean up went relatively smooth=
ly.=20

For those that could not make it to my Eagle Project, we have a few Life Sco=
uts that are currently working on theirs so you can support them when their t=
ime comes!

I=E2=80=99d like to especially thank Mr. Tragarz, Mr. Chow, Mr. Juarez, and a=
ll the other adults for helping the project move smoothly especially with po=
wer tools involved. Without the adults, the project would have been virtuall=
y impossible to succeed.

Once again, thank you to everyone that made it and everyone that planned to c=
ome!

Sincerely,

Kevin Cho=

emails.From: "'Kevin Cho' via All Parents and Scouts" <Team@bsatroop737.org>
emails.Subject: Eagle Project Success and Thanks
emails.Body:
Hello Troop! I just wanted to thank everyone that helped today in my Eagle P=
roject and also to those that could not make it but intended to. We actually=
 managed to finish the entire project 2 hours ahead of schedule thanks to th=
e dedication and support of both the scouts and adults. I=E2=80=99d like to e=
specially thank Mr. Tragarz, Mr. Chow, and the other adults for their above a=
nd beyond support; the project would not have been possible without them.=20=


For those that could not make it to my Eagle Project, we will have more oppo=
rtunities in the troop to participate in Eagle Projects and I highly suggest=
 doing so and supporting our troop=E2=80=99s Life Scouts to become Eagle Ran=
k!

Thank you all again!
Sincerely,

Kevin Cho=

 group the last few years! They will be leaving college sometime in August a=

>=20

 need to be addressed.
>=20
> God bless you all for your faithfulness!
>=20
> Patricia
>=20

Rich

Congratulations on joining Family Echo!

Family Echo connects you with your family - Past, Present and Future:

Past: Build your interactive family tree, going back far into the past.
Present: Share contact details and interests with cousins and beyond.
Future: Create a family record to pass on to future generations.

Your Family Echo username is: EvanT

By joining Family Echo, you have activated the following features:

  * Save your family tree for future access.
  * Add photos to bring your family to life.
  * Share and collaborate with invited relatives.
  * Download your family to your own computer.

If you forget your password, a new one will be emailed to this address.

We hope you enjoy Family Echo, and please don't hesitate to send your comments and suggestions by clicking 'Send Feedback' on the site!

Stay connected,
